ilings annually has spread more than  km  mi down the ok tedi and fly rivers raising river beds and causing flooding sediment deposition forest damage and a serious decline in the areas biodiversity the resulting devastation caused by the mining of ok tedi has included the loss of fish a vital food source for the local community loss of forest and crops due to flooding and the loss of areas of deep spiritual value for villagers are now submerged in mine tailings social and environmental responsibilityedit a village flooded in the bento rodrigues dam disaster  the dam was a property of samarco a joint venture between vale and bhp billiton bhp billiton is listed as one of the  companies extracting and marketing fossil fuels that are responsible for twothirds of global greenhouse gas emissions since the beginning of the industrial age its cumulative emissions until  have been estimated at  mtcoe representing  of global industrial emissions between  and ranking it the th largest corporate polluter according to bhp billiton management  of these emissions are from direct operations while  are from products sold by the company bhp billiton has been voluntarily reporting its direct ghg emissions since  in  it was criticised in  for lobbying against carbon pricing in australia bhp billiton voluntarily donates one per cent of pretax profit calculated on the average of the previous three years’ pretax profit in community programs and made us million of community donations including a us million contribution to bhp billiton corporate charitable entities bhp billiton is a founding partner and cofunder with the australian government of bush blitz operated by australian biological resources study with earthwatch australia significant accidentsedit inclement weather caused a bhp billiton helicopter to crash in angola on  november  killing the helicopters five passengers the dead were bhp billiton angola chief operating officer david hopgood australian angola technical services operations manager kevin ayre british wild dog helicopters pilot kottie breedt south african guy sommerfield of mmc british and louwrens prinsloo of prinsloo drilling namibian the helicopter went down approximately  kilometres  mi from alto cuilo exploration facility in north eastern angola bhp billiton responded by suspending operations in the country on  november  a dam holding back waste water from an iron ore mine in mariana southeastern brazil owned by bhp billiton and vale collapsed devastating a nearby town with mudslides killing at least  people injuring more than  and causing enormous ecological damage and threatening life along the river rio doce and the atlantic sea near the mouth of the rio doce the accident was the biggest environmental disaster in brazils history see alsoedit mining in australia referencesedit  a b our structure bhp billiton retrieved  august    a b c bhp billiton limited  annual report form k pdf edgar united states securities and exchange commission retrieved  april    about us bhp billiton retrieved  april    a b bhp billiton merger confirmed wwwabcnetau  march  retrieved  april    australia to block elliotts bhp listing plan marketwatch retrieved    robins brian  bhp to drop billiton in rebranding move the sydney morning herald retrieved    big australian just bhp again no billiton the sydney morning herald retrieved    a b c d billiton history wwwbhpbillitoncom retrieved  april    overview thaisarco retrieved  march    shell unit sells assets to gencor new york times  july  retrieved  april    gencor pops champagne btimescoza retrieved  april    bhp billiton energy coal south africa proprietary limited private company information  bloomberg wwwbloombergcom retrieved    subscribe to read wwwftcom retrieved    subscribe to read wwwftcom retrieved    south says output on track  iol retrieved    katy barnato  worlds largest mining firm records worst loss in its history cnbccom retrieved    hoyle rhiannon bhp billiton lays out petroleum ex