llion  operating income us billion  profit us billion  number of employees   website wwwbhpbillitoncom the former bhp billiton logo bhp the trading entity of bhp billiton limited and bhp billiton plc and formerly known as bhp billiton is an angloaustralian multinational mining metals and petroleum duallisted public company headquartered in melbourne victoria australia founded in  in the isolated mining town of broken hill it was the worlds largest mining company measured by  market values and australias fourth largest company by revenue formerly the largest bhp billiton was formed in  through the merger of the australian broken hill proprietary company limited bhp and the anglo–dutch billiton plc the result is a duallisted company the australiaregistered bhp billiton limited which has equal financial share in the company has a primary listing on the australian securities exchange and is one of the largest companies in australia measured by market capitalisation the englishregistered bhp billiton plc has a primary listing on the london stock exchange and is a constituent of the ftse  index in april  activist hedge fund manager elliott advisors proposed a plan for bhp to spin off its american petroleum assets and significantly restructure the business including the scrapping of its dual sydneylondon listing suggesting shares be offered only in the united kingdom while leaving its headquarters and tax residences in australia where shares would trade as depositary instruments at the time of the correspondence elliott held about  percent of the issued shares in londonlisted bhp billiton plc worth  billion australias government warned it would block moves to shift bhps stock listing from australia to the united kingdom australian treasurer scott morrison said the move would be contrary to the countrys national interest and would breach government orders mandating a listing on the australian securities exchange bhp dismissed the plan saying the costs and risks of elliotts proposal outweighed any potential benefits in may  with much of the former billiton assets having been disposed of bhp billiton began to rebrand itself as bhp at first in australia and then globally it replaced the slogan the big australian with think big with an advertising campaign rolling out in mid may  work on the change began in  according to bhps chief external affairs officer bhps global headquarters and australian registered corporate office is located at  collins street melbourne australia contents  history  billiton  broken hill proprietary company  bhp billiton  corporate affairs  senior management  operations  current  mines and facilities  former  social and environmental responsibility  significant accidents  see also  references  external links historyedit billitonedit the former billiton logo billiton was a mining company whose origins stretch back to  september  when the articles of association were approved by a meeting of shareholders in the groot keizerhof hotel in the hague the netherlands two months later the company acquired the mineral rights to the tinrich billiton belitung and bangka islands in the netherlands indies archipelago off the eastern coast of sumatra billitons initial business forays included tin and lead smelting in the netherlands followed in the s by bauxite mining in indonesia and suriname in  shell acquired billiton accelerated this growth the tin and lead smelter in arnhem the netherlands was shut down in the s billiton owned a tin smelting and refining plant in phuket thailand called thaisarco short for thailand smelting and refining company limited which still exists today in  south africas gencor ltd acquired the mining division of billiton excluding the downstream metal division billiton was divested from gencor in  in  billiton plc became a constituent of the ftse  index throughout the s and beyond billiton plc experienced considerable growth its portfolio included aluminium smelters in south africa and mozambique nickel operations in australia and colombia base metals mines in south america canada and south africa coal mines in australia colombia and south africa as well as interests in operations in brazil suriname australia aluminium and south africa titanium minerals and steel and ferroalloys in  billiton plc merged with the broken hill proprietary company limited bhp to form bhp billiton in  bhp billiton spun off a number of its subsidiaries in south africa and southern africa to form a new company known as south south is invested in manganese production and coal mining activities in south africa brazil australia and the far east in august  the company recorded its worst annual loss in history  billion towards the end of  bhp indicated it would be expanding its petroleum business with new investments in the sector broken hill proprietary companyedit the former broken hill proprietary company logo the broken hill proprietary company limited bhp also known by the nickname the big australian was incorporated in  operating the silver and lead mine at broken hill in western new south wales australia the broken hill group floated on  august  the first consignment of broken hill ore  tons  cwt grs was smelted at the intercolonial smelting and refining companys works at spotswood melbourne the resulting  ounces of silver raised a lot of interest when exhibited at the city of melbourne bank in collins st some sceptics asserted the promoters were merely using silver from somewhere else to ramp up the sharesanother shareholder the dominating wr wilson had had to lend william jamieson general manager a new suit so he could take the first prospectus printed at silverton near broken hill on  june  to adelaide to start the float process the geographic broken hill for which the town was named was discovered and named by charles sturt and created much interest among prospectors but nothing of note was discovered until charles rasp boundary rider for the encompassing mount gipps station pegged out a acre claim with contractors david james and james poole then with halfadozen backers the syndicate of seven including station manager george mcculloch a young cousin of victorian premier sir james mcculloch formed the broken hill company to stake out the whole hill in the ensuing months of fruitless search and with costs mounting several of the original seven parted with their shares and at the eve of the companys great success there were nine shareholders including rasp mcculloch william jamieson who bought up shares from several of the founders philip charley david james james poole bowes kelly and w r wilson john darling jr became a director of the company in  and was chairman of directors from  to  in  the company ventured into steel manufacturing with its operations based primarily in newcastle new south wales the decision to move from mining ore at broken hill to open a steelworks at newcastle was due to the technical limitations in recovering value from mining the lowerlying sulphide ores the discovery of iron knob and iron monarch near the western shore of the spencer gulf in south australia combined with the development by the bhp metallurgist a d carmichael of a technique for separating zinc sulphides from the accompanying earth and rock led bhp to implement the startlingly simple and cheap process for liberating vast amounts of valuable metals out of sulphide ores including huge heaps of tailings and slimes up to  ft  m high the company began petroleum exploration in the s with discoveries in bass strait an activity which became an increasing focus bhp began to diversify offshore in a variety of projects one project was the ok tedi copper mine in papua new guinea where the company was successfully sued by the indigenous inhabitants because of the environmental degradation caused by the mine operations bhp had better success with the giant escondida copper mine in chile  percent owned and the ekati diamond mine in northern canada which it divested in  to dominion diamond corporation formerly harry winston diamond corporation the inefficiencies of what was by global standards a small steel operation in newcastle finally caught up with the company and the newcastle operations were closed in  the long products side of the steel business was spun off to form onesteel in  bhp billitonedit diesel locomotives in bhp billiton iron ore bubble livery at the companys nelson point yard port hedland western australia in  bhp merged with the billiton mining company to form bhp billiton in  the flat products steel business was spun off to form bhp steel in  bhp steel changed its name to bluescope steel in march  bhp billiton announced a us billion agreed bid for another mining company wmc resources owners of the olympic dam copper gold and uranium mine in south australia nickel operations in western australia and queensland and a fertiliser plant also in queensland the takeover achieved  percent acceptance on  june  and  percent ownership was announced on  august  achieved through compulsory acquisition of the last  percent of the shares on  november  bhp billiton announced it was seeking to purchase rival mining group rio tinto group in an allshare deal the initial offer of  shares of bhp billiton stock for each share of rio tinto was rejected by the board of rio tinto for significantly undervaluing the company it was unknown at the time whether bhp billiton would attempt to purchase rio tinto through some form of hostile takeover however ceo marius kloppers met with many of rios shareholders following the announcement and reiterated that the offer for rio was compelling and that bhp billiton is very patient a formal hostile bid of  bhp billiton shares for each rio tinto share was announced on  february  the bid was withdrawn on  november  due to a global recession on  may  bhp billiton shares rose to a record high of a after speculation that chinese mining firm chinalco was considering purchasing a large stake bhp billiton representatives had no comment on  november  billiton announced that it would drop its a billion takeover of rival rio tinto group saying that the risks to shareholder value would increase to an unacceptable level due to the global financial crisis on  january  the company announced that in response to the global financial crisis the bhp billiton ravensthorpe nickel project in western australia would cease operations with a resultant discontinuation of shipments of ore from ravensthorpe to the yabulu nickel plant in queensland australia subsequently the yabulu refinery was sold to queensland billionaire mr clive palmer additionally the pinto valley mine in the united states was closed in total  employees were laid off including those laid off with the scaling back at some other projects on  december  bhp billiton sold its ravensthorpe nickel mine which cost a billion to build to vancouverbased first quantum minerals for us million first quantum was one of three bidders for the mine and actually produced the lowest offer the canadian company plans to have the mine back in production in mid ravensthorpe cost bhp us billion in writedowns when it was shut in january  after less than a year of production in january  after bhp billiton bought athabasca potash for usm the economist reported that by  bhp billiton could produce approximately  percent of the world demand for potash in august  bhp billiton made a hostile takeover bid worth us billion for the potash corporation of saskatchewan the bid came after bhps first bid made on  august was rejected as being undervalued this acquisition marked a major strategic move by bhp outside hard commodities and commenced the diversification of its business away from resources with high exposure to carbon price risk coal petroleum iron ore the takeover bid was opposed by the government of saskatchewan under premier brad wall on  november canadian industry minister tony clement announced the preliminary rejection of the deal under the investment canada act giving bhp billiton  days to refine their deal before a final decision was made on  november  the company announced that it was dropping its offer for potash corporation of saskatchewan on  february  bhp announced that it paid  billion in cash to chesapeake energy corp for all of the companys fayetteville shale assets which include  acres  km of mineral rights leases and  miles  km of pipeline located in north central arkansas in the united states the wells on the mineral leases are currently producing about  million cubic feet of natural gas per day bhp plans to spend  million to  billion a year over  years to develop the field and triple production on  july  bhp billiton announced that it would acquire petrohawk energy of the united states for approximately  billion in cash considerably expanding its shale natural gas resources in an offer of us per share in august  bhp billiton announced that it was shelving its us billion £ billion olympic dam copper and uranium mine expansion project in south australia as a result of falling commodity prices and slowing global economic growth the company simultaneously announced a freeze on approving any major new expansion projects days after announcing the olympic dam pullout bhp announced that it was selling its yeelirrie uranium project to canadian cameco for a fee of around  million the sale was part of a broader move to step away from resource expansion in australia on  august  bhp billiton announced it would create an independent global metals and mining company based on a selection of its aluminium coal manganese nickel and silver assets the newly formed entity named south was subsequently demerged with listings on the australian securities exchange the jse and the london stock exchange bhp billiton agreed to pay a fine of  million to the united states securities and exchange commission in  in connection with violations of the foreign corrupt practices act related to its hospitality program at the  summer olympics in beijing bhp billiton invited  government and stateowned enterprise officials to attend the games on an allexpensespaid package while bhp billiton claimed to have compliance processes in place to avoid conflicts of interest the sec found that bhp billiton had invited officials from at least four countries where bhp billiton had interests in influencing the officials decisions congo guinea philippines and burundi in  bhp billiton announced a billion investment in the new bp platform in the gulf of mexico during the same year as part of their plan to increase productivity at the escondida mine in chile which is the worlds biggest copper mine bhp billiton attempted to get workers to accept a year pay freeze a  reduction in the endofconflict bonus offering and increased shift flexibility this resulted in a major workers strike and forced the company to declare ‘force majeure’ on two shipments which drove copper prices up by  corporate affairsedit the australian bhp billiton limited and the british bhp billiton plc are separately listed with separate shareholder bodies but they operate as one business with identical boards of directors and a single management structure the global headquarters of the bhp billiton group  bhp billiton limited australia are located in melbourne australia bhp billiton plc is located in london england bhp billiton also has offices in houston usa santiago perth brisbane kuala lumpur singapore and shanghai the companys shares trade on the following exchanges bhp billiton limited australia asx bhp us nyse bhp bhp billiton plc uk lse blt us nyse bbl south africa jse bil senior managementedit in  with the stock price at less than  per share bhp hired an american paul anderson to reconstruct the company anderson was successful in this and completed his fouryear stint with a merger between bhp and londonbased billiton the ceo position was passed to brian gilbertson of billiton but in  after just six months in the ceo role gilbertson abruptly stepped down and cited irreconcilable differences with the boards as the reason for his resignation upon gilbertsons departure chip goodyear an anderson protégé was appointed the new ceo and he continued in that role until his retirement on  september  with the stock price over  per share marius kloppers was goodyears successor following the end of kloppers tenure in  andrew mackenzie the chief executive of nonferrous assumed the role of ceo in response to investor demands and a diminishing mining boom bhp billiton announced in midapril  that mackenzies remuneration package would be  per cent less than that of kloppers—barry fitzgerald writing for the australian stated that the decision represented the introduction of a new era of austerity for the corporation operationsedit currentedit bhp operates a wide variety of mining processing and oil and gas production operations in over  countries employing approximately  people the company has four primary operational units with an optional fifth operational unit referred to as businesses coal copper iron ore petroleum potash at the end of fiscal year  bhp billiton produced more than  million barrels of oil equivalent mmboe  million tonnes mt of copper  mt of iron ore  mt of metallurgical coal and  mt of energy coal in addition it has subsidiary logistics companies bhp transport and logistics pty ltd incorporating the former bhp shipping and bhpb freight pty ltd mines and facilitiesedit drill rig at area c mine near newman western australia process facility at mount whaleback mine western australia false colour satellite image of escondida mine chile courtesy of nasa algeria ohanet gas field rod gas field australia area c mine western australia bass strait victoria  percent owned blackwater mine blackwater queensland  percent owned broadmeadow queensland eastern ridge western australia goonyella riverside queensland gregory griffin western australia  percent owned hunter region new south wales jimblebar western australia kalgoorlie western australia kambalda western australia kwinana western australia leinster western australia minerva offshore victoria  percent owned mount keith western australia mount whaleback western australia nickel west operations north west shelf venture western australia  percent lng phase  percent domestic gas phase olympic dam south australia orebodies   and  mine western australia peak downs queensland port hedland western australia saraji queensland yandi mine western australia yarrie mine western australia brazil samarco a jointventure with vale sa  ownership each it is responsible for the worst environmental disaster in the history of mining in brazil the collapse of two iron ore tailings dams in bento rodrigues a subdistrict of mariana canada jansen potash development project saskatchewan chile escondida cerro colorado spence colombia cerrejón coal mine in guajira department  percent owned mexico trion peru antamina trinidad  tobago angostura oil and gas field united states permian shale texas eagle ford shale texas haynesville shale louisiana fayetteville shale arkansas shale natural gas fields including the associated midstream pipeline system gulf of mexico oil and gas field shenzi  neptune fields resolution copper near superior arizona formeredit papua new guinea until  ok tedi mine copper cause of a largescale ecological disaster in the ok tedi and fly rivers united kingdom liverpool bay oil and gas field the united nations environment programme has noted that bhp’s ok tedi mine site’s uncontrolled discharge of  million tonnes of waste rock and mine tailings annually has spread more than  km  mi down the ok tedi and fly rivers raising river beds and causing flooding sediment deposition forest damage and a serious decline in the areas biodiversity the resulting devastation caused by the mining of ok tedi has included the loss of fish a vital food source for the local community loss of forest and crops due to flooding and the loss of areas of deep spiritual value for villagers are now submerged in mine tailings social and environmental responsibilityedit a village flooded in the bento rodrigues dam disaster  the dam was a property of samarco a joint venture between vale and bhp billiton bhp billiton is listed as one of the  companies extracting and marketing fossil fuels that are responsible for twothirds of global greenhouse gas emissions since the beginning of the industrial age its cumulative emissions until  have been estimated at  mtcoe representing  of global industrial emissions between  and ranking it the th largest corporate polluter according to bhp billiton management  of these emissions are from direct operations while  are from products sold by the company bhp billiton has been voluntarily reporting its direct ghg emissions since  in  it was criticised in  for lobbying against carbon pricing in australia bhp billiton voluntarily donates one per cent of pretax profit calculated on the average of the previous three years’ pretax profit in community programs and made us million of community donations including a us million contribution to bhp billiton corporate charitable entities bhp billiton is a founding partner and cofunder with the australian government of bush blitz operated by australian biological resources study with earthwatch australia significant accidentsedit inclement weather caused a bhp billiton helicopter to crash in angola on  november  killing the helicopters five passengers the dead were bhp billiton angola chief operating officer david hopgood australian angola technical services operations manager kevin ayre british wild dog helicopters pilot kottie breedt south african guy sommerfield of mmc british and louwrens prinsloo of prinsloo drilling namibian the helicopter went down approximately  kilometres  mi from alto cuilo exploration facility in north eastern angola bhp billiton responded by suspending operations in the country on  november  a dam holding back waste water from an iron ore mine in mariana southeastern brazil owned by bhp billiton and vale collapsed devastating a nearby town with mudslides killing at least  people injuring more than  and causing enormous ecological damage and threatening life along the river rio doce and the atlantic sea near the mouth of the rio doce the accident was the biggest environmental disaster in brazils history see alsoedit mining in australia referencesedit  a b our structure bhp billiton retrieved  august    a b c bhp billiton limited  annual report form k pdf edgar united states securities and exchange commission retrieved  april    about us bhp billiton retrieved  april    a b bhp billiton merger confirmed wwwabcnetau  march  retrieved  april    australia to block elliotts bhp listing plan marketwatch retrieved    robins brian  bhp to drop billiton in rebranding move the sydney morning herald retrieved    big australian just bhp again no billiton the sydney morning herald retrieved    a b c d billiton history wwwbhpbillitoncom retrieved  april    overview thaisarco retrieved  march    shell unit sells assets to gencor new york times  july  retrieved  april    gencor pops champagne btimescoza retrieved  april    bhp billiton energy coal south africa proprietary limited private company information  bloomberg wwwbloombergcom retrieved    subscribe to read wwwftcom retrieved    subscribe to read wwwftcom retrieved    south says output on track  iol retrieved    katy barnato  worlds largest mining firm records worst loss in its history cnbccom retrieved    hoyle rhiannon bhp billiton lays out petroleum expansion plans marketwatch retrieved    shrinking the big australian findarticlescom retrieved  april    australian business records gabrnetau retrieved  april    wendy lewis simon balderstone and john bowan  events that shaped australia new holland p  isbn    a b c jay christopher  a future more prosperous the history of newcastle steelworks – the broken hill proprietary company limi